The Hindu Widows' Remarriage Act, 1856-The Act legalized remarriage of Hindu widows in certain cases and declared their rights and disabilities on remarriage.   3\. The Child Marriage Restrain Act, 1929 (Sharda Act).- The Act related to the restraints on the solemnisation of child marriages.   4\. The Guardians and Wards Act, 1890.- It applied to appointment of guardians by the Court.   So far many personal law has been reforming and supersedes for the betterment of the India.. As of now in Hindu law there are 26 ( twenty six) different Acts which have been passed.
